Here is the reframed code for the `sendMessage` method and the else block with the removal of `fileType` parameter:

```java
public void sendMessage(ResponseEntity response, boolean isSuccess, Exception e) {
    UnifiedAuditMessage auditMsg = new UnifiedAuditMessage();
    auditMsg.setInputFilePath(this.inputFilePath);
    auditMsg.setUrl(this.url);
    auditMsg.setPort(this.port);
    auditMsg.setOutputFilePath(this.outputFilePath);
    auditMsg.setDelimiters(this.delimiters);
    auditMsg.setFileType(this.fileType);
    auditMsg.setDate_received(DateTime.now());
    auditMsg.setDate_processed(isSuccess ? DateTime.now() : null);
    auditMsg.setNo_of_records_in_the_file(0);
    auditMsg.setNo_of_records_processed(0);
    auditMsg.setNo_of_records_failed(0);
    auditMsg.setJob_status(isSuccess ? JobStatus.COLLECTION_SUCCESSFUL : JobStatus.COLLECTION_FAILED);
    auditMsg.setJob_id(UUID.randomUUID());
    auditMsg.setJar_id(UUID.randomUUID());
    if (response != null) {
        auditMsg.setExceptions(List.of(response.getStatusCode().toString()));
    } else if (e != null) {
        auditMsg.setExceptions(List.of(e.getMessage()));
    }
    Logger.info(String.format("%s message sent %s", isSuccess ? "Success" : "Failure", auditMsg));
    this.writeMessage(auditMsg);
}

...

else {
    LOGGER.info("Not Ok!!");
    
    UnifiedAuditMessage auditMsg = new UnifiedAuditMessage(this.inputFilePath, this.url, this.port, this.outputFilePath, this.delimiters, this.fileType,
            DateTime.now(), 0, 0, 0, UUID.randomUUID(), UUID.randomUUID(), this.collector_id,
            JobStatus.COLLECTION_FAILED);
    
    UnifiedAuditMessage auditData = kafkaConsumer.logMetadata(auditMsg, this.fileType, response);
    
    kafkaAuditProducer.sendMessage(response, false);
    
    kafkaConsumer.writeLogToFile(auditMsg, this.fileType, response, destinationFolderPath);
}
```

In the reframed code, the `sendMessage` method no longer expects the `fileType` parameter. Instead, it uses the `fileType` field of the class by referring to `this.fileType`. The `else` block also passes the appropriate parameters to the `sendMessage` method.